This document is an 'IBM Batch Report' for Batch Number 20, processed at the Bangor Vote Collection Point (ID 2178) in NSW, with a Report Date of June 15, 2016. It details the processing outcomes for 50 individual ballots. For every ballot within this batch, all listed checks—including `QualityAssurance Checked`, `Initials Checked`, `Official Mark Checked`, `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Formality Result Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Preferences Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, `BTL Preferences Checked`, and `BTL Mismatches`—are recorded as "OK".

The document's relevance to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] lies in its direct correspondence to the 'IBM Outputs' sought. As one of the 106 "IBM Batch Report" PDF files, it provides granular insight into the ballot processing workflow. Specifically, this report exemplifies a batch where all automated and manual checks were completed without detecting any anomalies or requiring specific `Verification Action` or `Formality Reason` entries, showing a "clean" processing outcome. This contrasts with the "HAS ISSUES" entries and alphanumeric codes (e.g., D2, Y9) frequently found in other reports, as highlighted in the request overview, thus offering a complete picture of both successful and exceptional ballot processing scenarios.
